I stand before you today as David Lambert, a 55-year-old individual who has no prior criminal record, apart from the disqualification from driving two months ago. I come before this court to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified.

I must admit that I find myself in an unfortunate position. I failed to fully comprehend the consequences of my actions and, regrettably, decided to drive to a supermarket despite being aware of the court's previous order. I recognize that this was a grave mistake and I am deeply embarrassed by my lack of judgment.

